[normal]Matthew Ellis[bold]Police and Crime Commissioner for Staffordshire[bold]December 2013[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]I, 
[normal]Matthew Ellis
[normal] Police and Crime Commissioner for Staffordshire
[normal] give notice that
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]I have set out below under the appropriate headings my interests which I am required to declare.  I have put “none” where I have no such interests under any heading. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]I recognise that it can be a criminal offence to:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](
[normal]i
[normal]) omit the information which ought to be given in this notice
[normal]:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](ii) provide information which is materially false or misleading;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](iii) fail to give further notices in order to:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]- bring up to date information given in this notice
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]             
[normal]- declare an interest which I acquire after the date of this notice and have to 
[normal]               
[normal]declare.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In this document:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“body in which the relevant person has a beneficial interest” means a firm in which the relevant person is a partner or a body corporate of which the relevant person is a director, or in the securities of which the relevant person has a beneficial interest;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“director” includes a member of the committee of management of an industrial and provident society;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“land” includes an easement, servitude, interest or right in or over land which does not carry with it a right for the relevant person (alone or jointly with another) to occupy the land or to receive income;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] “elected local policing body” means the elected Local Policing Body to which the relevant person has been elected.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“relevant period” means the period of 12 months ending with the day on which the relevant person makes an entry amendment or deletion to the register of disclosable interests.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“relevant person” means the person(s) who is/are elected/appointed Police and Crime Commissioner and Deputy Police and Crime Commissioner.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“securities” means shares, debentures, debenture stock, loan stock, bonds, units of a collective investment scheme within the meaning of the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000(b) and other securities of any description, other than money deposited with a building society.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]1.  Employment, office, trade, profession or vocation[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Disclosable interest:
[normal] 
[normal]Any employment, office, trade, profession or vocation carried on for profit or gain.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]County Councillor for Lichfield Rural East (until April 2013)[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Owner of properties outside Staffs Border for rental incomes [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Disclosable interest: 
[normal]Any payment or provision of any other financial benefit (other than from the elected local policing body) made or provided within the relevant period in respect of any expenses incurred in carrying out duties and responsibilities, as of a Police or Deputy Police and Crime Commissioner, or towards the election expenses of the PCC or Deputy PCC.  This includes any payment or financial benefit from a trade union within the meaning of the Trade Union and Labour Relations (Consolidation) Act 1992(a).  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]N/A. None.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.  Contracts [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Disclosable interest: 
[normal]Any contract which is made between the relevant person (or a body in which the relevant person has a beneficial interest) and the elected local policing body –
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a) under which goods or services are to be provided or works are to be executed; and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b) which has not been fully discharged
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Staffordshire County Council[bold] Member (until April 2013)[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]4.  Land[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Disclosable interest: 
[normal]Any beneficial interest in land which is within the area of the elected local policing body
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Owner of a property in Shenstone, Staffordshire.[bold]5.  Licences[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Disclosable interest: 
[normal]Any licence (alone or jointly with others) to occupy land in the area of the elected local policing body.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]None[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6.  Corporate tenancies[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Disclosable interest: 
[normal]Any tenancy where (to the knowledge of the relevant person)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a) the landlord is the elected local policing body; and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b) the tenant is a body in which the relevant person has a beneficial interest.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]None[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7.  Securities[bold] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Disclosable interest: 
[normal]Any beneficial interest in securities of a body where –
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a) that body (to the relevant person’ knowledge) has a place of business or land in the area of the elected local policing body; and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b) either –
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](
[normal]i
[normal]) the total nominal value of the securities exceeds £25,000 or one hundredth of the total issued share capital of that body, or
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](ii) if the share capital of that body is of more than one class, the total nominal value of the shares of any one class in which the relevant person has a beneficial interest exceeds one hundredth of the total issued share capital of that class
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]None.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.  Gifts and Hospitality[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The interests of any person from whom the relevant person has received a gift or hospitality with an estimated value of at least £25.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]None.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]NB[bold]: A separate Gifts and Hospitality Register has been established to record any gift ort hospitality received during the period up to 31 March 2013.
